
@startuml sequence-diagram
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #222
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor white
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #222
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #222

title Sequence Diagram — Login · Order Creation · Password Reset

participant "Client" as C
participant "FastAPI\n/auth + /orders" as API
participant "Auth\nMiddleware" as AUTH
participant "ML Service\nRandomForest" as ML
participant "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Resend\nEmail" as EMAIL

== Login Flow ==
C -> API : POST /auth/token\n{ username, password }
API -> AUTH : validate credentials
AUTH -> DB : SELECT FROM users WHERE username=?
DB --> AUTH : user record
AUTH --> API : bcrypt.verify() → valid
API -> DB : UPDATE last_login
API --> C : 200 OK { access_token, role }

== Order Creation ==
C -> API : POST /orders/\nBearer token + order data
API -> AUTH : verify JWT token
API -> DB : SELECT branch + supplier
DB --> API : entities found
API -> ML : predict_delay(params)
ML --> API : { risk_class, probability }
API -> DB : INSERT order + order_items
API -> DB : UPDATE inventory (deduct stock)
API -> DB : check reorder_point alerts
API --> C : 201 Created { order, delay_risk }

== Password Reset ==
C -> API : POST /auth/forgot-password\n{ email }
API -> DB : INSERT reset_token (expires 1hr)
API -> EMAIL : send reset email via Resend API
API --> C : 200 OK { "If email exists, reset sent" }
@enduml